How to Compile The Amaya Opengl Version
===================================


Download External Library : freetype
------------------------------------

In order to render fonts, the opengl version use the Freetype library, 
which can be found at www.freetype.org.
You may download the latest source distribution
 and compile it on your system.
On Linux platform, you can get the binary and the developpement package
of you distribution instead.
Make sure the library and its headers are in the library path and 
the include path, so that the compilers can find them.


Compilation
-----------

On Linux, apart that you must run specific option for the configure, 
you must follow http://www.w3.org/Amaya/User/Autoconf.html instructions.
run the configure like this
#mkdir GL
#cd GL
#../configure --with-gl --with-gtk
(you can use --with-mesa option instead of --with-gl to compile with mesa library)

On Windows, open the amaya.dsw that is in the "windowsGL" subdirectory 
of source distribution, and follow the instructions at 
http://www.w3.org/Amaya/User/Win-Compiling.html


